    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent. | Railway Station | Orpington. S.E.R.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>July 19<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>My dear Litchfield</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>You are the best &amp; kindest man in the world.</p>
<p>I sh<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>. never have understood what to do, had you not so clearly explained everything.— I will follow your instructions to the letter &amp; hope to despatch the papers tomorrow<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>Yours affectionately | C. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            
            
             
            
            
        </div>
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the printed stationery, which is of a sort that CD used from November 1874; he died in April 1882.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">What CD was consulting Litchfield about is unknown; Litchfield was a barrister.</note>
        </div>
    
